Title: The March Towards Poverty: Why the Labour Government has much more to deal with than the economic consequences of Covid-19 in its upcoming budget
Abstract: This article examines the structural and policy-driven challenges facing New Zealand’s Labour Government beyond the immediate economic fallout of Covid-19. It argues that long-term welfare dependency, declining productivity, and unsustainable fiscal commitments pose deeper threats to economic resilience. The authors advocate for reforms in welfare, education, and public finance to reverse the trajectory toward poverty.
