Title: Determinants of access to basic handwashing facilities in developing countries: Implications for public health in the wake of COVID-19
Abstract: This paper analyzes the determinants of access to basic handwashing facilities across developing countries using cross-country data. It identifies income level, education, urbanization, and governance quality as key factors influencing hygiene infrastructure. The study underscores the importance of targeted investments in sanitation to mitigate future public health crises.
